OL,3,CDozens of MPs still working as
OL,4,Ccouncillors, despite calls to step down
OL,6,FLabour previously promised to ban all
OL,7,Fsecond jobs but has rowed back on that
OL,8,Fpledge, instead focusing on closing
OL,9,Floopholes that allowed politicians to
OL,10,Fdo paid advisory work or consultancy.
OL,12,FBut on councillor jobs, the Labour
OL,13,Frulebook specifically states that when
OL,14,FLabour MPs are elected to parliament
OL,15,Fthey have to give up their local
OL,16,Fcouncil seats "on a date agreed with
OL,17,Fthe Commons Chief Whip and General
OL,18,FSecretary".
